        "dcterms:title": "Every holospace object is OWNABLE — the 'Own' era on the content-addressed substrate (ADR-053): a Title is a signed, content-addressed claim (owner did:holo ⊕ owned κ ⊕ prior Title; rights as ODRL; a W3C VC) whose head κ proves the whole ownership history; transfer is a UCAN-attenuated, signed, conscience-gated capability op (a non-owner or an escalation is refused — SEC-2/L5); a double-transfer fork is detected and scarcity is anchored to an existing chain BY REFERENCE, never minted (Law L4); value settles against proven title (ADR-048); community ownership is a multi-principal Title — uniting web2 · web3 · AI in one self-verifying substrate"
      },
